        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 1:28AM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 127 AM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was 8 miles southeast of Arch,
or 20 miles southeast of Portales, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Hail up to penny size.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Maple.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Light accumulations of small hail will be possible, and could cause
slick and hazardous driving conditions. Consider moving to a sturdy
shelter until this storm passes.</instruction>
